result.name: Oliver's Super Sandwiches

reviews.text:
Nice little sandwich shop in Hong Kong, where I'm visiting. Here is my review on it.

Short review: Food can be okay to great, good staff service, good environment, clean, loud, not too pricey.

Food: Depending on what you order, it can be okay to great. I ordered a dish with a sausage, guava juice, eggs, tomatoes, raisins and pancakes. Sausage was okay, but felt a little fake, scrambled eggs with the tomatoes and raisins were nicely textured, and the pancakes were excellent. Very nice texture, good flavour. 

Service: Just wow. Food came in literally a minute. 3 dishes of it. Staff was also pretty friendly, and did their job well.

Environment: Feels very nice and comfortable. Not much to say here.

Price: Not too expensive. Standard price. 

Verdict: Pretty happy with this place, and it had always been one of my favorites if I visit Hong Kong. Recommend going here, and definitely recommend trying a sandwich here. Trust me, you won't regret it.
A little bit expensive but with fair food quality. I like the baked potato. However, don't expect too much for the coffee.
